sql:
SELECT ai_models.model_name, model_performance.metric, model_performance.value
FROM ai_models
JOIN model_performance ON ai_models.model_id = model_performance.model_id;

SELECT images.image_path, guesses.confidence
FROM images
JOIN guesses ON images.image_id = guesses.image_id;

SELECT im.image_category_id, ic.category_name, im.image_description
FROM images im
LEFT JOIN image_categories ic ON im.image_category_id = ic.category_id;

SELECT model_type, COUNT(model_id) AS total_models
FROM ai_models
GROUP BY model_type;

external_knowledge:
- "sea of confidence" symbolizes the average confidence level;
- "naming wave" refers to each category of images;
- "AI's belief" is the confidence the AI model has in its guesses;
- "seas of imagery" represents the various categories of images.

sql:
SELECT feedback_type, COUNT(*)
FROM feedback
GROUP BY feedback_type;

SELECT i.image_id, i.image_category_id
FROM images i
JOIN guesses g ON i.image_id = g.image_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'hidden tags' refers to the image labels;
- 'waters' metaphorically represents the complex layers of the database;
- 'treasures tied to the whispers of the AI' refers to the guesses made by AI models;
- 'echoes of the human heart' represents the user feedback or reactions;
- 'reflections in the mirror' refers to the original images reflecting their categories;
- 'roots of the botanical garden' symbolizes the connection to the image category;
- 'fabric of reality' metaphorically refers to the AI models;
- 'echoes of the past' symbolizes the datasets these images belong to.

- 'Model1' refers to a specific AI model;
- 'Category1' represents a particular category in the database;
- 'Image1' describes a specific image, considered a mystical artifact in this metaphorical context.

sql:
SELECT AVG(value) AS average_accuracy
FROM model_performance
WHERE model_id = 1 AND metric = 'accuracy';

external_knowledge:
- 'shining star' metaphorically refers to the model with the highest precision;
- 'constellation of precision' represents the set of AI models evaluated based on precision;
- 'highest peak of precision' corresponds to the maximum precision value among all precision metrics;

sql:
SELECT user_name, role
FROM users
WHERE user_id < 5;

external_knowledge:
- 'most active' in this context means the model with the highest count of unique guesses (`guess_id`).;
- The activity level is defined by the frequency of guess-making.;
- 'models' refer to different AI models identified by their unique `model_id`.;

sql:
SELECT COUNT(guess_id)
FROM guesses
WHERE confidence > 0.85;

SELECT model_description
FROM ai_models
WHERE model_name = 'Object Detector';

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM feedback
WHERE feedback_type = 'negative' AND feedback LIKE '%dog%';

SELECT i.image_id, i.image_category_id, ic.category_name
FROM images i
INNER JOIN image_categories ic ON i.image_category_id = ic.category_id;
